com.gpluscb.challonge_listener.listener

Class ListenerManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gpluscb.challonge_listener.listener.ListenerManager

  • public class ListenerManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The heart of this project. Requests all the tournaments specified by the listeners at specific intervals and compares all of the tournaments. If a difference is found, GenericEvents are fired to all managed EventListeners that are subscribed to the tournament the event is from. Events exist for all theoretically possible properties, including events that will never be fired like TournamentIdChangedEvent. If the id of a tournament really changed, it would not be seen as the same tournament anymore, therefore a TournamentDeletedEvent would be fired rather than a TournamentIdChangedEvent.

    The manager can be in various states, the states progress as follows:

    • INITIALIZING
    • RUNNING
    • SHUTTING_DOWN
    • SHUT_DOWN

      • ListenerManager

        public ListenerManager(ChallongeExtension challonge,
                       long interval)
                throws at.stefangeyer.challonge.exception.DataAccessException
        Creates a running instance that tries to update at the specified interval. Note that if something is changed but then changed back in-between updates the changes may not fire events.
        The instance will run until the shutdown() method is called or the garbage collector destroys it.
        Parameters:
        challonge - The ChallongeExtension instance used to get all the tournament data
        interval - The interval to try to update at in milliseconds. If the interval is 0, the manager tries to update as quickly as possible
        Throws:
        at.stefangeyer.challonge.exception.DataAccessException - Exchange with the rest api or validation failed
